		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Jan 22nd 2:46 AM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=98013141832481&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=98013141832481&num=2&page=&post=1&replyto=98013141832481"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98013141832481></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=21176"><span id=>Jevitz</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>5 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hey<br>Alright, where should I go to hunt at level 15-17. I was at Siren Island and got good xp until the level 54 Druid helping me out suddenly got attacked by Brawn and Dragoon. And they stayed there. So then I headed over to Unrest which I dont like. So where should a level 15 go to hunt? At level 17 I am heading over to Lake of Ill Omen. Well, thats all. Thanks&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Jevitz Endavi<br>Druid of the 24rd Season<br>Terris Thule<br>Order of Loyalty</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Jan 22nd 6:51 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=98013141832481&num=2&page=&post=1&replyto=98018930823969"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98018930823969></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Hello fellow Druid.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just dinged 17 on my woody druid on Luclin.  Anyway, heres what I found about 15-17...<br><br>Oasis- Okay, everybody says it's terribly camped and it was until they added dungeon faction bonuses.  Before, 70-80 people peaked in Oasis on a weekend night (Might be more on other servers cause ours' is now green) but now the most thats ever on is around 20-30.  You have basically 3 options for Oasis-<br>   1. Solo- I recommend soloing scarabs, tarantulas, caimans, and crocs by doing this:  Grasping Roots, Stinging Swarm (make sure u kept that conjuration up!; also, i heard that when u kite, dots only work to 60% of their maximum value.) Meditate to get back the mana casted from Stinging swarm, and then ignite and/or melee to the death.  (One tip- try to trade SoW's with clarity that the high lvl enchanters that wait on the docks for boats to Kunark.  They make solo'ing faster and easier!)<br>   2.  Get into a croc group.  The best I can recommend is to just partner with 1 war or monk.  Each of your skills complements each other well.<br>   3.  Orc group- OK, this isnt the greatest experience, but it does have decent loot and there are always 20+ orcs running around on that highway.  THE BIGGER THE GROUP THE BETTER FOR THESE.<br><br>Lavastorm- A little known, to me anyways =), place which connects Nektulos to a druid ring, entrances to Najena, Temple of Sol Ro, and Nagafen.  Most likely you'll have to pass through Nektulos to get here.  YOU ARE KOS TO NEKTULOS GUARDS, BUT they can't see through your lvl 4 spell camo =).  All u have to do is to keep running in the generally straight direction from the entrance in EC to the exit in Lavastorm.  The path forks but u can always tell which path points straight ahead.  Anyways, back to the point.  When u enter Lavastorm, hug the wall to the right until u come to a zone entrance that has broken wooden doors on the ground.  This is Najena, and is safer to zone into here because if u zone into nek when u get into trouble sometimes people accidentally train guards to the lavastorm zone at the same time =(.  So stay by Najena zone and fight there.  This zone is very underutilized and the fire elementals are quite nice.  I recommend fighting the fire elementals for a few reasons (I have tooooooo many reasons for everything):<br>   1.  Everything in this zone resists Ignite, so by fighting elementals u can use your expulse summoned here and take them down easy with the the grasping roots, stinging swarm, and expulse summoned method.<br>   2.  Ignite does like 37 damamge, but expulse summoned does around 74 i believe =).<br>   <br>   If your not completely bored by now I hope you and other druids got something out of this post.  Have fun, and save the trees.<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
