		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=17062"><span id=Scholar>Sezule</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>23 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>East Karana is your place for a kiting extravaganza.&nbsp;&nbsp;I leveled from 14-20 here, (boring, I know) but the vast difference in MOB's to hunt is great.  Go for carrion spiders (be careful of poison) chasm crawlers (ditto).  Just have to be careful of the gorge hounds, which will probably still be blue at 21.  East Karana is NOT overpopulated by any means.  Just find a place to hunt, and kite away.   Be careful of lions while you med, they will attack you without warning.  (Good idea to listen for footsteps)  As you level to 16 or 17, they only become minor annoyances.  Having another druid partner is great if you don't want to solo.  A necro is also a good coice.<br><br>One thing on your idea to go to Lake of Ill Omen at 17--I went there at 21 and it was great fighting.  I suggest going there at 19 or 20.  17 isn't too low, but I'm thinking most things will be red to you.  A good place to group up at level 17, so it could be a good choice if you're not a fan of soloing, or want a break.<br><br>Good luck to you!  I highly recommend you try East Karana, and props on your choice of Ill Omen, it's a great place to hunt!  Be safe, Tunare be with you.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
